{{BLP sources|date=February 2012}} {{Infobox person | name = Rafael del Pino Calvo-Sotelo | image = Rafael-del-Pino-Calvo-Sotelo.jpg | caption = | birth_date = 14 July 1958 | birth_place = [[Madrid]], Spain | nationality = Spanish | occupation = [[Executive president]] of [[Ferrovial]] | residence = | alma_mater = [[MIT Sloan School of Management]] | signature = | net worth = $1.12 billion (forbes) | parents = [[Rafael del Pino (businessman)|Rafael del Pino y Moreno]] | children = | relations = [[Maria del Pino y Calvo-Sotelo]] (sister) }}
'''Rafael del Pino Calvo-Sotelo''' (born 1958), is a Spanish [[billionaire]] businessman, the executive chairman of [[Ferrovial]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ferrovial.com/en/IR-Shareholders/Corporate-Governance-/Board-of-Directors- |title=Ferrovial Board of Directors }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ferrovial.com/en/Our-Company/Chairman-Rafael-del-Pino |title=Chairman – Rafael del Pino}}</ref> the company founded in 1952 by his father [[Rafael del Pino (Spaniard)|Rafael del Pino Moreno]].
He graduated as a civil engineer from the Polytechnic University of Madrid (1981). He also holds an MBA from the [[MIT Sloan School of Management]] (1986). He was the chief executive officer (CEO) of Grupo Ferrovial from 1992 to 1999.
Rafael del Pino is a member of the [[MIT Corporation]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://web.mit.edu/corporation/members/delPino-R.html |title=MIT Corporation Membership – Rafael del Pino}}</ref> the MIT Energy Initiative’s External Advisory Board<ref>{{cite web |url=https://mitei.mit.edu/about/external-advisory-board |title=MIT Energy Initiative External Advisory Board |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424174004/https://mitei.mit.edu/about/external-advisory-board |archivedate=2014-04-24 |df= }}</ref> and MIT Sloan’s European Advisory Board.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mitsloan.mit.edu/about/emsaeb-members.php |title=MIT Sloan Executive Boards}}</ref> In addition he is a member of the International Advisory Board of [[IESE]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iese.edu/en/about-iese/governance/ |title=IESE International Advisory Board (IAB)}}</ref> and of the [[Harvard Business School]] European Advisory Board.
He is the nephew of former [[Spanish PM]] [[Leopoldo Calvo-Sotelo]].
