'''Ziya Bazhayev''' (July 11, 1960 - March 9, 2000) was a prominent [[Russia]]n businessman of [[Chechen people|Chechen]] origin specializing in oil trading. He died in [[Moscow]] during a crash of a [[Yakovlev Yak-40]] aircraft shortly after take off on March 9, 2000, together with a Russian journalist, [[Artyom Borovik]].

Bazhayev's death is mentioned in many [[Advance-fee fraud|Nigerian 419 scam]] e-mails.<ref>[http://www.419baiter.com/_scam_emails/08-08d/scam-email-35236.html DR AL-FUHARD MOHAMMED for one Late Mr. Ziya Bazhayev a Russian] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090621015023/http://www.419baiter.com/_scam_emails/08-08d/scam-email-35236.html |date=June 21, 2009 }} 419eater.com</ref>

